  </data>
  <data name="GeneralTranscribeCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Start and stop transcription. The text is copied to the clipboard.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralPrimaryRewriteCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Primary rewrite</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralPrimaryRewriteCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Transcribe, then rewrite with the primary profile. Choose the profile on the Rewriting page.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralSecondaryRewriteCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Secondary rewrite</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralSecondaryRewriteCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Transcribe, then rewrite with the secondary profile. Choose the profile on the Rewriting page.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAppThemeCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>App theme</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAppThemeCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Light, dark, or follow your Windows theme.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralThemeSystem.Content" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>System</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralThemeLight.Content" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Light</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralThemeDark.Content" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Dark</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAutostartCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Start with Windows</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAutostartCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Launch Deckle automatically when you sign in.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralWarmupCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Warm up Whisper at launch</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralWarmupCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Run a silent transcription at startup so the first real recording is fast. Costs a few seconds of GPU at launch.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralMicrophoneCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Microphone</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralMicrophoneCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Audio input device used for recording. Default: system default.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAutoPasteCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Auto-paste after transcription</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAutoPasteCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Also tries to paste into the focused field. The paste is strict and only fires when the target can be safely confirmed — so it rarely triggers. The clipboard is always the reliable path.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelExpander.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Voice level window</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelExpander.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The dBFS range the recording HUD uses to map your microphone signal onto the on-screen level. Calibrate once against your mic and forget it, or let auto-calibration update it from your measured percentiles.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelAutoLabel.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Auto</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelFloorCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Floor</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelFloorCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Below this level, the HUD reads silence. Set just under the percentile of your normal pauses (typical: -55 dBFS).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelCeilingCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Ceiling</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelCeilingCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>At or above this level, the HUD saturates. Set just below your loudest peaks (typical: -32 dBFS).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelCurveCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Curve</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralVoiceLevelCurveCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Shape of the response between floor and ceiling. 1.0 = linear (recommended). Higher = compress quiet, expand loud. Lower = the opposite.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayExpander.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Show the overlay while recording</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayExpander.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>A small floating indicator shown at the bottom of your screen while Deckle captures and transcribes.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayFadeCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Fade when your cursor is near</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayFadeCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Make the overlay transparent when you move over it, so it never blocks what's underneath.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayAnimationsCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Animate transitions</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayAnimationsCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Smoothly slide and fade the overlay and message cards. Stays on even when Windows reduced-motion is enabled, because those transitions help you track which message replaced which.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayPositionCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Screen position</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayPositionCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Where the overlay appears on your primary display. Applied on the next recording.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayPositionTop.Content" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Top</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralOverlayPositionBottom.Content" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Bottom</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralLogMicrophoneCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Log microphone</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralLogMicrophoneCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>At the end of every recording, log the RMS distribution of your microphone (min, percentiles, max in dBFS) to the LogWindow and to microphone.jsonl. Useful when calibrating the level window.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralLatencyCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Latency</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralLatencyCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Record per-step timings of each transcription — voice detection, Whisper, rewrite, clipboard, paste — to latency.jsonl. Timings only, no transcript text.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAppLogCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Application log</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAppLogCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Mirror every in-app log line to app.jsonl to diagnose a specific issue across restarts. Verbose — around 2 MB per 30 min of active use. Rotates every 5000 lines (app-1.jsonl, app-2.jsonl, …).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralCorpusExpander.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Corpus</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralCorpusExpander.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Save every transcription as a JSONL line under a per-profile subfolder (one corpus.jsonl per rewrite profile). Text only — for offline prompt tuning and analysis.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAudioCorpusCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Also save audio (WAV)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralAudioCorpusCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Keep the raw 16 kHz mono audio of each recording alongside the JSONL, in an audio/ subfolder per profile. Roughly 2 MB per minute of speech.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralStorageFolderCard.Header" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Storage folder</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralStorageFolderCard.Description" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Shared root for every telemetry stream enabled above. Leave empty to use the default %LOCALAPPDATA%\Deckle\telemetry\.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralStorageFolderSetLabel.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Set</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GeneralStorageFolderSetButton.ToolTipService.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
